cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.DB. 

The paper proposes a framework for improving performance in distantly-supervised relation extraction, which is a task in natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of document structure and label propagation techniques could also place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DB (Databases) sub-categories.
